The United States strongly condemns the terrorist attack on a police headquarters in southeastern Turkey, which was claimed by the PKK. This attack is part of an alarming trend of increasing violence by the PKK in Turkey. The US also condemns the attack on the convoy of Kemal Kilicdaroglu, the leader of Turkey's main opposition party. The US sends condolences to the families of those killed and wishes a speedy recovery to those injured. They continue to support Turkey, a NATO ally, in its fight against terrorism and are working closely with Turkish authorities.